import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='open', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data, label='Closing Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day_name()
    avg_volume_per_day = data.groupby('day')['volume'].mean().reset_index()

    chart = sns.barplot(x='day', y='volume', data=avg_volume_per_day)
    plt.title('What is the average volume traded per day?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day of the Week')
    plt.ylabel('Average Volume Traded')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Days', loc='upper right', labels=avg_volume_per_day['day'].unique())

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['daily_change'] = data['Close'] - data['Open']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='daily_change', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['daily_change'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['daily_change'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily price changes?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
